&lt;p class=MsoNormal align=center style='margin-right:-.5in;text-align:center'>&lt;b>&lt;span
lang=DA style='font-size:14.0pt'>INDWELLING SIN: ROMANS 7&lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class=MsoNormal align=center style='margin-right:-.5in;text-align:center'>&lt;b>&lt;span
lang=DA style='font-size:12.0pt'>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class=MsoNormal align=center style='margin-right:-.5in;text-align:center'>&lt;span
lang=DA style='font-size:12.0pt'>Virgil Warren, PhD&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class=MsoNormal style='margin-right:-.5in;text-align:justify'>&lt;b>&lt;span
lang=DA style='font-size:12.0pt'>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class=MsoNormal style='margin-right:-.5in;text-align:justify'>&lt;b>&lt;span
lang=DA style='font-size:12.0pt'>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class=MsoNormal style='margin-right:-.5in;text-align:justify'>&lt;span lang=DA
style='font-size:12.0pt'>            &lt;/span>&lt;span style='font-size:12.0pt'>When
Paul speaks of sin resident within him (or indwelling sin), perhaps he means it
phenomenologically; that is, the experience of sin feels like something inside him.
His point is that sin is not just &lt;u>something outside us&lt;/u> (environment,
influence) trying to tempt us into misaction; it is &lt;u>something inside us&lt;/u>
as well. There is a subjective as well as objective component in the sin
phenomenon. The implication is personal responsibility for subjective response
to objective influence and stimulus.&lt;/span>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>ITEMS AFFECTED BY THE DOCTRINE OF NATURAL DEPRAVITY</title><link>https://christir.org/essays/topics/christian-doctrine/mankind-anthropology/depravity/items-affected-by-the-doctrine-of-natural-depravity/</link><pubDate>Thu, 02 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/essays/topics/christian-doctrine/mankind-anthropology/depravity/items-affected-by-the-doctrine-of-natural-depravity/</guid><description>&lt;style>
